#### [NEW] [LiveAnalysis.tsx](file:///c:/Users/hp/Desktop/Et-AI_Hack/ET-AI-Hack/frontend/src/components/sentinel/LiveAnalysis.tsx)

WebRTC live analysis component:
- `navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ audio: true, video: optional })` 
- `MediaRecorder` API captures audio chunks (WebM/opus)
- Chunks sent to backend via WebSocket every 2–3 seconds
- Backend runs STT + analysis on each chunk
- Results streamed back via WebSocket
- Visual layout:
  - Left panel: Audio waveform + optional video preview
  - Right panel: Live transcript + threat gauge + intent badges
  - Bottom: Session controls (start/stop, mute, video toggle)

**Audio Pipeline (Browser Side)**:
```
getUserMedia → MediaRecorder (timeslice=3000ms) 
  → onDataAvailable → WebSocket.send(blob)
  → receive analysis updates → update UI
```

**Backend Side** (handled by `sentinel_ws.py`):
```
Receive audio chunk → write to temp buffer
  → when buffer > 3s: run Faster-Whisper STT
  → classify transcript → update threat score
  → broadcast StreamUpdate via WebSocket
```

